  "prompt": "Instagram (product): How do I quickly unfollow people on Instagram?",
  "response": "To quickly unfollow people on Instagram, you can follow these steps:\n\n### Method 1: Unfollowing from the Profile\n1. **Open Instagram App**: Launch the Instagram app on your device.\n2. **Go to Your Profile**: Tap on your profile picture at the bottom right corner.\n3. **Tap Following**: Tap on the \u201cFollowing\u201d section to see the list of accounts you're following.\n4. **Unfollow**: Scroll through the list and tap the \u201cFollowing\u201d button next to the accounts you want to unfollow. This will change to \u201cFollow,\u201d indicating you've unfollowed them.\n\n### Method 2: Unfollowing from the Home Feed\n1. **Go to Your Feed**: Open your Instagram feed.\n2. **Find a Post from the Account**: Scroll through your feed and find a post from the person you want to unfollow.\n3. **Tap on Their Username**: Tap on the username to access their profile.\n4. **Unfollow**: Tap the \u201cFollowing\u201d button and confirm to unfollow.\n\n### Method 3: Bulk Unfollowing (Using a Third-party Tool)\n- Note that using third-party apps to manage your Instagram can violate Instagram's terms of service and could result in account restrictions. Use caution!\n\n### Additional Tips:\n- **Limited Actions**: Instagram may limit the number of accounts you can unfollow in a single day to prevent spammy behavior. If you hit a limit, you might need to wait a few hours or until the next day to unfollow more accounts.\n- **Unfollow from Settings**: You can also go to Settings > Security > Account Data > \u201cConnections\u201d where you may find more management options, depending on the Instagram version.\n\n### Conclusion\nThese methods will help you quickly unfollow accounts on Instagram. Remember to take breaks if you're unfollowing many accounts to stay within Instagram\u2019s guidelines.",
